<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="315" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.9411/177</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Japanese Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Japanese Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Pursuant to instructions from Viscount
                            Motono, I have the honor to inform you that Viscount Kikujiro Ishii,
                            former Minister for Foreign Affairs, was on June 13 appointed to be
                            Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary and ordered to proceed to
                            the United States. His suite will be composed of Isamu Takeshita, Vice
                            Admiral, I. J. N.; Hisaichi Sugano, Major General, I. J. A.; Matsuzo
                            Nagai, Secretary of the Foreign Office; Masataka Ando, Commander, I. J.
                            N.; Seiji Tanikawa, Infantry Major, I. J. A.; and Tadanao Imai, Vice
                            Consul.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Aimaro Sato</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>